- Engagement effectiveness is a measure of how well users respond to task assignment notifications by posting comments; 
- A higher effectiveness ratio indicates better engagement; 
- Percentile ranking allows for comparison of users' effectiveness relative to their peers.

- A user is considered active if they have engaged with notifications or have completed tasks; 
- Task completion efficiency is measured by the average days to complete tasks and the average time since task creation and last update;
- Average days to completion is calculated only for completed tasks.
